text: H. australis may refer to: * Haageocereus australis, the Quisco De La Costa De Aric, a cactus species endemic to southern Peru and northern Chile * Hemiandra australis, a shrub species in the genus Hemiandra found in Australia * Hoya australis, the waxvine or common waxflower, a plant species found in Australia ==See also== * Australis (disambiguation)
title: H. australis
